unittitle_ssm: Andrea Callard Papers
abstract_ssm: The Andrea Callard Papers include materials relating to the downtown New York art scene in the late 1970s and 1980s. The collection contains a particularly rich series on Collaborative Projects, Inc. (Colab), a non-profit arts group which Andrea Callard helped create. Additionally, the collection includes research, drawing, painting, and photography related to Andrea Callard's professional art career. Finally, the collection contains a great deal of information on art education residencies throughout New York.
